  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed operating points and the UQ campaign included one-at-a-time parameter sweeps that informed factor gap identification. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed; 7 factors achieved levels below required levels and 6 factors were flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Despite the UQ campaign findings, the structured sensitivity analysis artefact has not been formally linked to this package. Decision: Accepted based on compensating controls and regulatory risk-benefit determination.",
