    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/hemolysis-bench-5pt",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Five-point hemolysis bench validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (nIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 operating conditions. Mean absolute error 18.4%; model over-predicts hemolysis at high-speed low-flow conditions. The UQ campaign (Monte Carlo, n=512 samples) quantified combined input uncertainty at ±22% nIH (95% CI). One-at-a-time sensitivity sweeps were conducted during the UQ campaign and documented in the project technical report, informing factor gap identification but not formally registered as a structured sensitivity analysis artefact in this credibility package."
    },
    {
