      "name": "Grid convergence index study — three-mesh Richardson extrapolation",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study yielding GCI of 4.7% on nIH at the nominal operating point. Discretization error is within acceptable bounds for MRL 5 at gradation 2 but required level is 3."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/code-verification-mms",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Method of manufactured solutions — Navier-Stokes solver verification",
      "description": "Second-order spatial convergence confirmed for velocity and pressure fields. Hemolysis transport equation verified to first-order convergence consistent with upwind discretization scheme."
    }
  ],
