  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou2-accepted-compensating",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/regulatory-submission-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite 7 of 13 credibility factors achieving levels below required levels and 6 factors flagged as epistemic gaps, the submission is accepted under compensating risk-benefit controls. The Monte Carlo UQ campaign (n=512, ±22% nIH at 95% CI) demonstrates that the model systematically over-predicts hemolysis, providing a conservative safety margin relative to the clinical threshold. Regulatory precedent for the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry provides additional confidence. Residual epistemic gaps in model form, test samples, and equivalency of input parameters are acknowledged; a post-market surveillance commitment is recorded to resolve these gaps in the next design iteration. The UQ campaign included one-at-a-time sensitivity sweeps informing factor gap identification; these findings are documented in the project technical report.",
